title: Twenty Three Years Later by Charlie Donlea
author: Wen

sentences.content: Cameron - man found murdered in his home
Detective - homicide detective hand-picked to solve this murder
Victoria Ford - woman accused of this murder because her DNA was  found.
2 Months later she dies in 9/11 attack.
Greg - scientist at New York medical examiner office who identifies  Victoria's remains
Mack Carter - Anchor who died and Avery replaced on TV show Christine- Avery's executive producer
Mosley Germaine - head of Network for Avery's show
In 2001, A rich man is murdered in Catskills
His Lover is accused of murder 2 months later
Lover dies in the September 11th Attacks
20 years Later on, her remains are identified in 2021
A TV anchor hears about this and is interested in covering  the story but not for obvious reasons
TV anchor attends a party with 40 others and will negotiate  with her boss about her future job and stories to cover...
A Wealthy man, Cameron, is found murdered in his mansion.
This crime scene was made to look like he had ended his own life.
A special Detective uncovered different clues that point to a woman  being present the night before.
They process the murder scene in great detail.
On September 11th, Victoria Ford meets with her attorney in the top  floor of an office building.
He says there's heavy DNA evidence tying her to the murder of  Cameron: rope from her car on him, her fingerprints, her blood, and  her urine.
Victoria denies involvement, other than being his lover and having an  affair.
She needs 1 million dollars for her bail before next week.
Suddenly she sees out of the corner of her eye, an airplane strike a  building nearby and the entire office shake and crumble around her.
She will not survive.
20 Years Later in year 2021.
a scientist named Greg is working at the  New York medical examiner's office.
He is testing bone fragments recovered from victims of the 9/11  Attacks.
He takes the DNA codes from bones he's tested, and then inputs it into  a databank system to hope to identify the names of victims.
For 3 years they've never had a match.
Until today, he identified  Victoria Ford.
Her parents are dead but her sister could be contacted.
They run the test again to be certain before making the call.
Avery Mason is the main character this book will follow.
She is a famous entertainment news anchor.
She replaced a treasured  news anchor, Mack, who died suddenly.
She reports true crime and survivor stories.
But she is most excited about a future story, about a woman in New  York who died in the 9/11 attacks but was identified using new  technology.
At least this is what she wants people to believe.
Today Avery is escaping a sinking car and being filmed doing it.
Mack, her predecessor, had performed it years before, and that TV  episode had inspired a Mom on how she would in real life, to save  herself and children.
Avery reenacts this and successfully escapes.
Avery reveals she is very interested in reporting on news story about  9/11 in New York's medical examiner office identifying a woman, but  not for reasons one would assume.
Avery attends a dinner party with 39 others at the home of the head of  the television network.
The network head lives in a large home on the beach.
Avery has strategically dressed and planned for a conversation she  must have with Mosley about her contract.
She rejected a contract  offer last week and needs to negotiate.
She plans to avoid others for the beginning of the party (except for her  producer who she speaks with).
She will approach him at the right  moment.
Was is important to begin this story with the murder  scene.Yes or No?
Do we know much about the man murdered in 2001?
And What few things do we know about the Detective in 2001?
Avery is the main character in 2021What is the name of her  television program?
At least that's what she wanted them to think...
What may Avery  be hiding about why she is REALLY interested in the 9/11 story?
What do you think will occur directly next, at this party Avery is at?
Does anyone recall Avery's drink of choice at the party?
